25/02/2008
TIRANA, Albania -- NATO will continue to support the progress of the Albanian armed forces by providing experts and training, the new commander of NATO's Allied Joint Force Command in Naples, Admiral Mark Fitzgerald, said on Friday (February 22nd) at a meeting with Prime Minister Sali Berisha in Tirana. 
Berisha said the two major priorities of his government are integration into the EU and NATO. 
He praised the level of co-operation among political parties in achieving important reforms required by the two organisations. 
(Albanian Prime Minister website, Balkanweb, Top-Channel - 22/02/08)
